<TEXT>
moslem guerrillas fired rockets and 
heavy artillery into the eastern city of jalalabad but afghan 
troops returned fire and forced the guerrillas to retreat a 
government spokesman said wednesday 
also wednesday iranbased guerrilla leaders were quoted as 
saying plans were under way for an offensive near kabul 
in singapore an afghan resistance leader gulbuddin hekmatyar 
said the resistance plans to shift its interim government this week 
from pakistan to the liberated afghanistan provinces of kunar 
and paktia 
hekmatyar foreign minister of the interim government set up in 
february by several guerrilla groups told a news conference 
wednesday that the entire cabinet would move within the next two 
to three days some ministries to asadabad capital of kunar and 
others to a site still be decided in paktia 
hekmatyar was in singapore on an eightnation tour to seek 
recognition for his government malaysia announced tuesday if will 
formally recognize the interim government 
mohammad karim khalili spokesman of the iranbased guerrillas 
said at a news conference in tehran that forces in the city of 
meidan near kabul and in ghazi and areas to the north of the 
capital are preparing to start operations and soon a new front 
will be opened near kabul tehran radio reported 
the guerrillas are split into the iranbased shiite coalition 
and the larger sunni alliance based in pakistan the two have been 
at odds over the formation of a guerrilla government in which the 
shiite alliance is not represented 
an unidentified official of the shiite alliance was quoted by 
irans official islamic republic news agency as saying that plans 
to attack kabul have been drawn up and efforts are under way to 
unite all mujahedeen groups for delivering the coup de grace 
pakistanbased guerrilla groups have been engaged in heavy 
fighting for jalalabad since march 6 
foreign ministry spokesman mohammad nabi amani said 19 civilians 
died and 15 were wounded in the latest rebel attack on jalalabad 
45 miles from the border with pakistan 
government forces counterattacked and forced the opposition to 
halt their offensive and retreat he said 
amani said there were no casualties among government soldiers 
he said 271 guerrillas were killed and 201 were injured 
the information could not be independently confirmed 
the guerrillas known as mujahedeen or islamic holy warriors 
have been fighting nearly 11 years to topple afghanistans marxist 
government 
capturing jalalabad is considered a key element in their 
strategy because it would give the guerrillas their first major 
urban foothold 
amani also said un checkpoints will be set up at six points 
along the afghanpakistani border to check for aid afghanistan 
alleges is flowing to the guerrillas illegally from pakistan 
pakistan agreed tuesday to allow the un to set up permanent 
monitoring posts along the border it denies the afghan allegations 
the checkpoints will be manned by the un good office mission 
to afghanistan and pakistan which monitored the withdrawal of 
soviet troops from afghanistan 
in iran khalili said the iranbased forces oppose the un 
deployment 
rasul sayyaf prime minister of the rebels provisional 
government told un secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar on 
wednesday to stay clear of what he called a dying kabul 
governments desperate tactic to draw the security council into a 
domestic war 
in a letter he asked the un chief to preempt a security 
council debate and if that was not possible then to steer the 
debate on the right course russian interference in afghanistan 
afghanistans ruling marxists charged in an emergency session of 
the security council tuesday that pakistan was waging a 
fullfledged war against kabul and intervening in the war by 
sending pakistani army and milita to the battlefront pakistan 
denied these charges which have repeatedly been leveled by the 
kabul government 
