phyllis mensing day supervising editor in 
the chicago bureau of the associated press has been named 
correspondent in charge of the aps bismarck bureau 
the appointment was announced tuesday by tena haraldson chief 
of bureau for north dakota and south dakota 
mensing 39 joined the ap as a parttime newswoman while 
attending school at augustana college in sioux falls sd 
following graduation and a year teaching she rejoined the ap in 
sioux falls in 1972 other assignments took her to pierre sd 
minneapolis fargo nd where she served as correspondent and 
philadelphia 
mensing is a native of mapleton minn 
she succeeds philip brasher who will transfer to the aps 
washington bureau to be a regional reporter for minnesota north 
dakota and south dakota 
