tom bradley was the early leader in his 
campaign for a historic fifth term as mayor of the nations 
secondlargest city capturing 54 percent of the absentee vote in a 
race characterized by low voter turnout 
bradley 71 the citys first black mayor needed at least 50 
percent of the vote to avoid a june 6 runoff 
fortyfive minutes after the polls closed at 8 pm bradley was 
in the lead with 13146 absentee ballots or 54 percent according 
to the city clerks office 
the nextclosest contender was freshman city councilman nate 
holden who received 5014 absentee votes or 2066 percent former 
los angeles county supervisor and television commentator baxter 
ward had 4800 votes or 197 percent 
although virtually no observers believed the mayor could lose 
one newspaper reported that a secret poll conducted by bradleys 
campaign last week showed the mayor with just 53 percent of the 
vote 
