valery polyakov is scheduled for april 27 
the mir has been permanently manned since february 1987 when 
yuri romanenko and alexander laveikin boarded the spacecraft 
mir was launched into orbit in february 1986 soviets have said 
it is the first part of a permanently manned space station 
cosmonauts vladimir titov and musa manarov last dec 20 set a 
world record for space endurance living aboard the space station 
for 365 days and 22 hours 
volkov and krikalev arrived at the mir station on nov 26 as a 
