enjoys our full support as he implements courageous reform 
measures to strengthen egypts economy for future generations 
the statement added our cash transfer assistance will be part 
of that support we will be consulting with congress and working 
out the details of the release of the money in cooperation with the 
egyptian government 
aid to israel and to egypt was boosted after the two countries 
signed a peace treaty in 1979 since then the united states has 
been liberal in assisting the two countries as its most reliable 
friends in the middle east the aid also is a subtle way of 
encouraging israel and egypt to support us foreign policy in the 
region 
at the moment the bush administration is backing a proposal by 
israeli prime minister yitzhak shamir to hold elections among the 
14 million palestinian arabs who live on the west bank and in gaza 
mubarak has called instead for an international peace conference 
and said the palestine liberation organization should participate 
but mubarak has not rejected the proposal categorically 
