the dropout rate for public school students has 
leveled off over the past few years according to statistics 
released wednesday 
figures from the board of education for the 198788 school year 
show the fouryear dropout rate for high school students was 268 
percent and the systemwide percentage was 297 
these are up slightly from the year before when the high school 
rate was 263 percent and the systemwide figure was 292 percent 
a separate study that followed individuals for their four years 
of high school ending in 1988 said 208 percent of the students had 
dropped out in 1987 this study said 224 percent of students quit 
schools chancellor richard green said more funding is needed for 
dropout prevention programs 
the studies use separate methodologies to determine the dropout 
rate the cohort report follows students for four years after they 
enter ninth grade and the annual dropout report analyzes the 
students who dropped out during 198788 
the annual dropout report also offers a racial and ethnic 
breakdown and showed that the dropout rate among hispanic students 
was significantly higher than the average 
it said the fouryear systemwide dropout rate among hispanic 
students was 318 percent for blacks 245 percent whites 192 
percent and asians 152 percent 
