although human sacrifices were performed regularly in 
precolumbian times human ritual slayings are unheard of in 
modern mexico said fernando winfield capitaine director of the 
veracruz museum of anthropology in xalapa 
animal sacrifices are very common however as part of the 
widespread superstition and witchcraft that exists in mexico 
nowadays winfield said in a telephone interview 
police in matamoros just across the border from brownsville 
texas have uncovered more than a dozen human bodies apparently 
used by drug smugglers practicing voodoo rites popularly known as 
santeria 
the smugglers apparently tried to offer the souls of others 
human and animal to protect themselves from arrest and harm 
police had arrested several people and were looking on wednesday 
