here are major provisions of president bushs 
proposals wednesday to tighten ethics rules for judges members of 
congress and the executive branch 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed a 25 percent pay increase for federal judges 
coupled with a ban on acceptance of speaking fees and other 
honoraria associate justices of the supreme court for example 
would see their salaries rise from 110000 to 137000 while us 
district court judges pay would go to 111900 from 89500 
bush said he supported pay hikes and a honoraria ban for 
congress but did not make a specific proposal 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed a ban on the use of leftover campaign 
contributions for personal use and office expenses the law now 
allows anyone who held office before 1980 to use such funds for any 
lawful purpose 
bush also called for a ban on campaign contributions by 
political action committees although he did not make a formal 
proposal on it he also said he opposes efforts to set up a federal 
fund for congressional races like the taxpayersupported one that 
is used for the presidential campaign 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
to tighten financial disclosure rules bush proposed a uniform 
system for the three branches of government requiring individuals 
to disclose the actual value of each asset and source of income 
rounded to the nearest thousand dollars currently individuals are 
required to report only within broad categories such as 5000 to 
15000 
more members of the executive branch also would have to file 
disclosure reports 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed to expand a law that forbids individuals in the 
executive branch from taking official actions that financially 
benefit them or members of their family he said it also should 
apply to the judiciary and employes of congress though not to 
congress members themselves 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
senior officials in all three branches of government would be 
barred from serving on the board of directors of forprofit 
enterprises 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
