to bankruptcy trustee david martin to pay creditors in the last 
major civil lawsuit against butcher 
a federal jury in knoxville last month found that ch butcher 
sr and two disbarred atlanta lawyers conspired to help the younger 
butcher keep some of his wealth 
the jury found the senior butcher robert l schwind and david 
l hill guilty under the racketeering influenced corrupt 
organizations act following a fourday trial 
ch butcher jr and his brother 1978 tennessee democratic 
gubernatorial candidate jake butcher were convicted in connection 
with the 1983 failure of their twin banking empires southern 
industrial banking corp and united american bank chain 
testimony included assertions that hill received 16 million 
from butcher jr to buy gold bars and coins after the financier had 
declared bankruptcy 
martin has been trying to locate the 16 million and documents 
produced at the trial showed that hill was the last person known to 
have handled it 
hill was not present at the trial he and schwind his former 
law partner were disbarred after their moneylaundering 
convictions in an unrelated case 
the jury awarded damages of 245437 from butcher sr 474288 
from schwind and 163 million from hill under a rico provision 
tripling that amount the total jury award was 7049176 
