<TEXT>
smithkline beckman corp and britains 
beecham group plc announced wednesday they would merge and form the 
worlds secondlargest pharmaceutical company but a wall street 
analyst warned that either firm could find itself a takeover target 
before the transaction is completed 
smithkline and beecham who confirmed earlier this month they 
were negotiating on a merger said they would exchange stock and 
establish a pharmaceutical and health care giant with estimated 
sales of 67 billion 
the new company to be named smithkline beecham would rank 
second in worldwide pharmaceutical sales behind merck amp co second 
in overthecounter medicines behind american home products corp 
and fourth in animal health 
the firm will have a research and development budget of more 
than 500 million per year smithkline chairman henry wendt said at 
a news conference 
we will have one of the best and largest research and 
development organizations in the world drawing on the scientific 
skills and traditions of the united states and britain he said 
under the merger agreement smithkline shareholders would 
receive five b shares of stock in the new company for each of 
their old shares and beecham shareholders would receive slightly 
less than one a share for each of their old shares 
the new shares would have equal voting rights in the affairs of 
smithkline beecham but dividends paid to each a share would be 
about five times the dividends paid to each b share 
smithkline currently has some 133 million shares outstanding and 
beecham has about 768 million shares outstanding 
two smithkline subsidiaries allergan an eye and skincare 
business and 84 percent of beckman instruments which makes 
diagnostic and laboratory equipment would be spun off to 
smithkline shareholders the companies said in a joint statement 
smithkline last fall sold 16 percent of beckman through a public 
stock offering 
beecham plans to sell off its cosmetics and fragrance divisions 
plus other nonpharmaceutical businesses officials said 
smithkline shareholders would receive a onetime cash dividend 
of 550 per share they also would get about half a share of 
allergan and about 018 shares of smithkline stock for each 
smithkline share according to a news release 
the merger would be subject to governmental approval and a vote 
by shareholders of both companies 
smithkline stock fell 2 in new york stock exchange composite 
trading wednesday closing at 6275 a share 
a financial analyst specializing in pharmaceutical companies 
said the merger announcement could draw new bids for either company 
before stockholders vote four months from now 
to quote yogi berra it isnt over till its over said 
